            "bestRating": "5",
            "worstRating": "1"
          },
          "reviewBody": "Admission process is sick It’s just for the sake of process… My son was able to get through the entrance written exam and as per process there should have been an interaction scheduled with school management. We missed the email on first day surprisingly there was no call made or any message sent across other than email however after 2 days later when we contacted the school basis the email we were told a reschedule of meeting would be made. But it was only verbal assurance as stated by them it’s a process if someone misses the first meeting they schedule the second one. Next week when I was not contacted by school we contacted the school and got to know admissions are full and there was no interaction for my child. It seems to be all misleading and false information given by school and they did not adhere the process they advised. It’s one of the worst experience we had for a school with the name of Cambridge.  Thank You",
          "publisher": {
            "@type": "Organization",
            "name": "Yellow Slate"
          }
